Additionally, the market is witnessing increased investments in research and development activities aimed at enhancing the efficiency, reliability, and scalability of energy harvesting systems. Companies are focusing on developing advanced transducers, power management integrated circuits, and energy storage elements to optimize energy conversion and storage capabilities. Furthermore, advancements in materials science and nanotechnology are enabling the development of next-generation energy harvesting technologies that offer higher power output and longer operational lifespans, driving market growth and innovation.

